STEP 1 — GET XRAY TOKEN
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
Run:

curl -s \
  -X POST \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"client_id":"XRAY_CLIENT_ID","client_secret":"XRAY_CLIENT_SECRET"}' \
  https://xray.cloud.getxray.app/api/v2/authenticate

Save returned token as XRAY_TOKEN.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
STEP 2 — GET ISSUE ID FOR EACH TEST KEY
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
Xray Cloud needs the internal issue ID (number),
not the issue key (TP-63).

For each unique Test Key in the CSV, run:

curl -s \
  -u "praveen@testable.cloud:JIRA_API_TOKEN" \
  "https://testable.atlassian.net/rest/api/3/issue/TP-63" \
  | grep -o '"id":"[0-9]*"' | head -1

Save the mapping:
  TP-63 → 11108
  TP-64 → 11109
  (repeat for all unique test keys in CSV)

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
STEP 3 — ADD TEST STEPS USING XRAY GraphQL
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
For each step row in the CSV, run this command
using the issue ID from Step 2:

curl -s \
  -X POST \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer XRAY_TOKEN" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "query": "mutation { addTestStep(issueId: \"<ISSUE_ID>\", step: { action: \"<ACTION>\", data: \"<DATA>\", result: \"<EXPECTED_RESULT>\" }) { id action data result } }"
  }' \
  https://xray.cloud.getxray.app/api/v2/graphql

Example for TP-63 Step 1:

curl -s \
  -X POST \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer XRAY_TOKEN" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "query": "mutation { addTestStep(issueId: \"11108\", step: { action: \"Navigate to /signin page\", data: \"https://app.testable.io/signin\", result: \"Sign-in page loads with all fields visible\" }) { id action data result } }"
  }' \
  https://xray.cloud.getxray.app/api/v2/graphql

Repeat this call for EVERY step row in the CSV.
Process all steps in order — Step 1 before Step 2.

